ap companies the fund invests in the stocks of socially conscious companies which are focused on environmental social and governance esg criteria it employs fundamental analysis with a bottomup stock picking approach focusing on factors such as current financial condition and industry position market economic political and regulatory conditions earnings assets cash flows allocation of capital favorable supplydemand conditions for key products development of new products or businesses competitive position in the marketplace quality of management and companies and other enterprises that demonstrate varying degrees of commitment and progress toward addressing key corporate responsibility and sustainability challenges to create its portfolio the fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the russell  value index and lipper largecap value funds average it conducts proprietary research to create its portfolio the fund does not invest in the stocks of companies that demonstrate poor environmental performance or compliance records contribute significantly to local or global environmental problems or include risks related to the operation of nuclear power facilities are the subjects of serious laborrelated actions or penalties by regulatory agencies exhibit a pattern and practice of human rights violations exhibit a pattern and practice of violating the rights and protections of indigenous peoples demonstrate poor corporate governance or engage in harmful or unethical business practices manufacture tobacco products have significant and direct involvement in the manufacture of alcoholic beverages or gambling operations manufacture or sell firearms andor ammunition abuse animals and develop geneticallymodified organisms for environmental release without countervailing social benefits it was formerly known as calvert sage fund  calvert large cap value fund calvert sage fund  calvert global value fund was formed on december   and is domiciled in the united states d